      "side": 1,
      "message": "We don\u0027t actually need the cached version here, because we\u0027re storing the result in a static. The Cached API primarily exists for situations where the caller can\u0027t guarantee that they\u0027ll keep the resulting object around (specifically, deserializing any runtime shader or color filter).",
